Copilot: A (Haskell DSL) stream language for generating hard real-time C code.

Maintainer          : Lee Pike <leepike@gmail.com>
Contributors        : Alwyn Goodloe, Robin Morisset, and Sebastian Niller
LICENSE             : BSD3
Academic paper      : http://www.cs.indiana.edu/~lepike/pub_pages/rv2010.html

Getting started: Copilot is a Haskell library, best installed using Cabal. It's
API is documented Language.Copilot.Help and is run by loading
Language.Copilot.Interface and running help. There are numerous examples in
Language.Copilot.Examples/ .
